    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-12-14T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-12-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="652"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d652">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">600.119/1912c: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Chargé in Great Britain</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Laughlin</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="30" xml:id="d652fn30">The same, on same date, to Embassies
                        in France (for McFadden, No. 497), Italy (for Stewart, No. 54), and Japan
                        (for Rabbitt, No. 159).</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-12-14">December 14,
                            1918</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>For Sheldon [from War Trade Board]: No. 1849. We will issue a general license,
                    effective December 16, known as R.A.C. 63, permitting <pb facs="0844" n="756"
                        xml:id="pg_756"/> the exportation without the issuance of individual
                    licenses of all commodities not on Conservation List to the United Kingdom,
                    France, Italy and Japan, including their colonies, possessions and
                    protectorates.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
